The paper deals with variations of the pancake flipping problem, which is a well-known problem in computer science and falls under the category of combinatorial optimization. The paper also mentions applications in interconnection networks and computational biology, which suggests that it may belong to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely sub-categories as they are directly related to the problem of sorting and optimization.
